                    <head xml:lang="en">
                        Acquisition of sources
                    </head>
                    <desc xml:lang="en" corresp="definition">
                        Depending on the type of object, a wide range of sources need to be collated and analysed. These sources can include: Fieldwork drawings (including old ones) Iconographic sources (from books, prints, artworks, etc.) Geographical data (surveys, maps, etc.) Text sources (descriptions, etc.) New photos  All the sources need to be digitised (in standard formats: e.g. JPEG for images; PDFs for texts; CSV) and organised in a clear tree structure.
                    </desc>
